The article argues in favor of cutting business taxes, specifically the corporate income tax. It criticizes Democrats for opposing a permanent cut in the corporate tax rate, despite supporting it when Barack Obama was in office. The article states that a low, uniform corporate tax rate is not corporate welfare, but rather a way to reduce economic distortions and make American businesses more competitive globally. It also emphasizes that real individuals, not corporations, ultimately pay the corporate income tax. The article concludes by criticizing Democrats for engaging in a bad-faith debate and serving their own ambitions instead of the common good.